OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe Chancellor also announced a
OL,8,Ffurther cut in national insurance,
OL,9,Freducing it from 10% to 8%.JHowever,
OL,10,Fthe Government has also insisted that
OL,11,Fthe powersharing Executive must raise
OL,12,Fits own revenue to write off Stormont
OL,13,Fdebt.JNorthern Ireland Secretary Chris
OL,14,FHeaton-Harris said the Budget
OL,15,Funderlined the Government's commitment
OL,16,Fto Northern Ireland.JHe said: "I
OL,17,Fwelcome the additional Barnett funding
OL,18,Fof #100 million for 2024-25, which is
OL,19,Fon top of the significant #3.3 billion
OL,20,Fspending settlement.J"This will
OL,21,Fprovide a further boost to the
OL,22,FExecutive's spending power to invest
OL,23,Fin its own priorities.J"I am delighted
OL,24,Fwith the Chancellor's announcement of
OL,25,Fover #1 billion of new tax reliefs for
OL,26,Fcreative industries across the UK,
